    "description": "Johnson & Johnson India Consulting Pvt Ltd is actively seeking a talented and motivated Radiologist to join our dynamic team in Visakhapatnam. This is an excellent opportunity for professionals who are passionate about making a real impact in a fast-growing organization.\n\nAbout Johnson & Johnson India Consulting Pvt Ltd:\nJohnson & Johnson India Consulting Pvt Ltd is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Diagnose and treat medical conditions following established protocols\n• Educate patients and families on health management and disease prevention\n• Collaborate with pharmaceutical representatives and medical suppliers\n• Coordinate with multidisciplinary teams for comprehensive patient management\n• Maintain accurate clinical documentation in electronic health records\n• Maintain sterile environments and follow infection control protocols\n• Adhere to NABH/JCI accreditation standards\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Com / M.Com / MBA Finance\n• 0-1 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in HIPAA Compliance\n• Proficiency in Clinical Documentation\n• Proficiency in CPT Codes\n• Proficiency in Patient Care\n• Proficiency in Telemedicine\n• Proficiency in Medical Terminology\n• Proficiency in Clinical Research\n• Proficiency in ICD-10\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Learning & development budget\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Flexible working hours\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Salary Range: 2.5 LPA - 6 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Visakhapatnam, Andhra Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Johnson & Johnson India Consulting Pvt Ltd!",
